Figure.4.21 Epiphysis
3. The Metaphysis: is the narrow portion of a long bone between the epiphysis and the diaphysis. It contains the growth plate, for growth during childhood; it is rich in blood supply which makes it prone to infection in childhood leading to osteomyelitis (Figure 4.22).
![](https://cdn.mathpix.com/cropped/2025_04_09_5c7058303e6d1c6ad4cfg-089.jpg?height=448&width=511&top_left_y=500&top_left_x=401)

