$\mathbf{1}^{\text {st }}$ Rib: is the shortest rib, it is flat and wider than other ribs. It has a small rounded head with one facet for articulation with its corresponding vertebrae. The superior and lateral surfaces are indented by two grooves for the subclavian vessels (Figure 7.6).
